            Shipping (Seafarers) (Allotments) Regulation</docTitle><enactingFormula>(<ref href="/hk/cap478/s89">Cap. 478, sections 89</ref> and
                <ref href="/hk/cap478/s134">134</ref>)</enactingFormula><sourceNote>(Enacting provision omitted—<ref href="hk/2020/er2">E.R. 2 of 2020</ref>)<marker role="blank-line"></marker><marker role="blank-line"></marker></sourceNote><commencementNote>[2 September
                1996]<inline class="width_3"></inline><sourceNote><ref href="/hk/1996/ln342">L.N. 342 of
            1996</ref></sourceNote></commencementNote><sourceNote>(Format changes—<ref href="hk/2020/er2">E.R. 2 of 2020</ref>)</sourceNote><section id="ID_1438403236342_002" name="s1" reason="omittedAsSpent" startPeriod="2020-03-19" status="omitted" temporalId="s1"><num value="1">1.</num><sourceNote>(Omitted as spent—<ref href="hk/2020/er2">E.R. 2 of 2020</ref>)</sourceNote></section><section id="ID_1438403236358_001" name="s2" reason="inEffect" startPeriod="2020-03-19" status="operational" temporalId="s2"><num value="2">2.</num><heading>Interpretation</heading><leadIn>In this Regulation, unless the context otherwise requires—</leadIn><def name="Ship"><term>ship</term>
                (<term xml:lang="zh-Hant-HK">船舶</term>) means a Hong Kong ship.</def></section><section id="ID_1438403236358_003" name="s3" reason="inEffect" startPeriod="2020-03-19" status="operational" temporalId="s3"><num value="3">3.</num><heading>Application</heading><content>This Regulation shall apply to every seafarer employed under a crew agreement.</content></section><section id="ID_1438403236373_001" name="s4" reason="inEffect" startPeriod="2020-03-19" status="operational" temporalId="s4"><num value="4">4.</num><heading>Circumstances in which a seafarer may make an allotment</heading><leadIn>Subject to
            section 5, a seafarer
            employed
            under a crew agreement relating to one or more ships who—
            <sourceNote>(<ref href="hk/2016/ln70">L.N. 70 of 2016</ref>)</sourceNote></leadIn><paragraph id="ID_1438412624077_012" name="a" temporalId="s4_a"><num value="a">(a)</num><content>is not exempted from the requirements of <ref>section 80</ref> of the Ordinance
                by regulations made under that section; or</content></paragraph><paragraph id="ID_1438412624077_020" name="b" temporalId="s4_b"><num value="b">(b)</num><content>is employed in a ship which is not exempted from those requirements by those
                regulations,</content></paragraph><continued>may at any time while he is so employed, by means of an allotment note issued in
            accordance with this Regulation, allot
            all or a
            part of his wages to any person or persons.
            <sourceNote>(<ref href="hk/2016/ln70">L.N. 70 of 2016</ref>)</sourceNote></continued></section><section id="ID_1438403236373_003" name="s5" reason="inEffect" startPeriod="2020-03-19" status="operational" temporalId="s5"><num value="5">5.</num><heading>Limitation on issue of allotment notes</heading><subsection id="ID_1438412624108_004" name="1" temporalId="s5_1"><num value="1">(1)</num><leadIn>Unless the seafarer’s employer or the master otherwise agrees, a seafarer
                employed to
                work on board a coastal-going ship shall not—
                <sourceNote>(<ref href="hk/2016/ln70">L.N. 70 of 2016</ref>)</sourceNote></leadIn><paragraph id="ID_1438412624108_012" name="a" temporalId="s5_1_a"><num value="a">(a)</num><content>allot more than one half of his wages; or</content></paragraph><paragraph id="ID_1438412624108_020" name="b" temporalId="s5_1_b"><num value="b">(b)</num><content>allot that part of his wages to more than 2 persons.</content></paragraph></subsection><subsection id="ID_1438412624108_027" name="2" temporalId="s5_2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content>For the purposes of calculating the proportion of a seafarer’s wages specified in subsection <ref>(1)(a)</ref>, the wages of the seafarer shall be taken to be his wages calculated at the rate stipulated in the crew agreement under which he is employed without any addition (including overtime payments) or deduction.</content></subsection></section><section id="ID_1438403236389_002" name="s6" reason="inEffect" startPeriod="2020-03-19" status="operational" temporalId="s6"><num value="6">6.</num><heading>Times and intervals of payments under allotment notes</heading><leadIn>Unless the seafarer’s employer or the master otherwise agrees—</leadIn><paragraph id="ID_1438412624124_049" name="a" temporalId="s6_a"><num value="a">(a)</num><content>the first sum payable under an allotment note shall be payable not less than 1 month from the date on which the allotment note is issued and subsequent sums shall become payable at regular intervals of not less than 1 month reckoned from the date when the first sum is payable; and</content></paragraph><paragraph id="ID_1438412624139_006" name="b" temporalId="s6_b"><num value="b">(b)</num><content>no sum shall be payable under an allotment note before the seafarer has earned
                any of the wages
                allotted
                by it.</content></paragraph></section><section id="ID_1438403236405_001" name="s7" reason="inEffect" startPeriod="2020-03-19" status="operational" temporalId="s7"><num value="7">7.</num><heading>Form of allotment notes</heading><subsection id="ID_1438412624155_004" name="1" temporalId="s7_1"><num value="1">(1)</num><content>An allotment note shall be in the form prescribed in the <ref>Schedule</ref>.</content></subsection><subsection id="ID_1438412624155_012" name="2" temporalId="s7_2"><num value="2">(2)</num><content>The Authority may, by notice published in the Gazette, amend the <ref>Schedule</ref>.</content></subsection></section><schedule id="ID_1438403236405_003" name="sch0" reason="inEffect" startPeriod="2020-03-19" status="operational" temporalId="sch0"><num value="0">Schedule</num><note class="align_right" role="crossReferences" type="inline">[<ref href="/hk/cap478A/s7">s. 7</ref>]</note><heading>Form of
